msDesc.head: Book of rents for the hospital in Vernon

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in ink and pencil.

p.note: Top of page, in black ink by a medieval hand: four lines of text in French; bottom left corner: National Library book label with current signum.

binding.p: Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 6 raised bands. , top of page in black ink: No 39. Reditus Domus Dei in vernone. , on a damaged label in ink: St-s, and in print: II REDITUS DOMUS DEI DE VERNONE; stamped: A 239; National Library book label with current signum.
binding.condition: Leather worn. , the leather possibly a later repair. and , repairs with white leather; , middle of cover, outer edge: 2 holes; upper part of cover: two nails (remnats of strap); : several holes and marks from a knife on the cover.

origin.p: France Vernon , 13th century, last quarter. For a discussion on the date see Louis (1997) page VII–VII.

provenance.p: The manuscript later belonged to Paul Petau, from whom it was acquired by Queen Christina and brought to Sweden. The signum on the corresponds to the catalogue of 1734 (125e), where it is listed as: Phil. in 4o no 39.
In the manuscript was on loan to Vernon.

p.note: Elaborate cross-like shape drawn in the outer margin in brown ink.
Additions in the margin or after the main text in ink by one or several medieval hands. The first two are short additions, while the one on is longer (8 lines).
Parchment note attached to with a metal pin (pin removed in the image). contains 7 lines of text in French written by a medieval hand, is blank.

decoDesc.p: Main text in black ink. The first letter in a new pargraph consists of a captal placed in a separate column in the outer margin, e.g. .

decoNote.p: : Penwork initial C over 5 lines (+ extending above the line) in black ink, penwork initial over 2 lines below the larger initial. : opening plain initial Q over 3 lines in black with interior reserved shapes; a face drawn in the counter space (possibly a later addition) and a guide letter in the margin. : plain initials over 2-4 lines in black.
